Somewhere, in some forum, on some board (if not this one) someone had a copy/paste directly from the developers on how Fizzles work.

Here's my try at recreating it...

You will fizzle any new spells.  The level YOU get the spell is important.  Just because your friend got the spell at level (for instance) 14, and you got it at 30...doesn't mean it will work very well for you right away.

You will fizzle a lot until you get more than the skill cap for the level you get the spell.  For instance, using your 180 skill level...that's max skill for a level 35.  Now, you're a hybrid, so you get spells at 30 and then at 39.

But, if you got that spell at 39...it's going to fizzle a LOT.  It won't stop fizzling all the time (you will fizzle - I fizzle level 9 spells at level 57) when you get your skill up to at least 200.

Understand?

